title: From teenage parent to retail grind, navigating the tough realities of life (ep 257)
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "So we had our child, right? Newly born. I started working at a retail clothing shop. I remember working and I was like working like long hours. It was insane. It was my first time working in such an environment. I knew that I needed to start making money for my child and the types of jobs in which you can get at such a young age with no experience are, you know, they're very limited. You could say. And so I was working quite hard at this job. And then I recall one afternoon specifically when I came home and then I was going through the mail and my father just happened to see me going through the mail because he knew I was looking for my check and I had found it. He came over and he asked me, what is that? And I said, that's my check. And he goes, open it. I was like, okay. So I opened my check and then I look at it and he looks at it too. And then he just like looks up at me and says, now, do you think that that's going to provide for your family?
